                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17039694" author="ankitraj" created="Wed, 19 Feb 2020 04:35:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i am working on this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17039749" author="ankitraj" created="Wed, 19 Feb 2020 06:58:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Jackey+Lee&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Jackey Lee&quot;&gt;Jackey Lee&lt;/a&gt;, you mean after add jar failed .show() statement also should throw exception ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040557" author="jackey lee" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 01:49:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Ankitraj&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Ankitraj&quot;&gt;Ankitraj&lt;/a&gt; No, I think we should just throw Exception once hive run statement failed. Otherwise, the user cannot detect that this statement has failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any jira you have created for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040795" author="ankitraj" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 09:30:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no i have not created any jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040803" author="ankitraj" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 09:42:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=srowen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;srowen&quot;&gt;srowen&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cloud_fan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cloud_fan&quot;&gt;cloud_fan&lt;/a&gt; please give your suggestion for this jira, according to me current behaviour is correct.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040822" author="jackey lee" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 10:06:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So your opinion is to return normal results even if the statement runs wrong? A bit weird, it is really unamiable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040834" author="ankitraj" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 10:40:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to me user should handle Exception case,during exception handling they can terminate application or can write log and continue further execution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyhow you already raised a PR let them review then it will clear to us.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17040868" author="jackey lee" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2020 11:18:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t agree more. It is up to the user to choose how to handle the exception. What Spark does is to inform the user about the exception, not to mask it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17041727" author="ankitraj" created="Fri, 21 Feb 2020 10:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Jackey+Lee&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Jackey Lee&quot;&gt;Jackey Lee&lt;/a&gt;, your point is correct , Thank you for raising pr&#160;&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
